6:
It's amazing you went this far into
the ocean, Razelt. That's quite the
sense of direction you have...
15:
Would you stop speaking of me like
a compass without a needle! And I
may be physically fine, but my heart
is in tatters!
18:
Hi there. I thought maybe you guys
were testing out were some kind of
newfangled mini-ship, but that was
your idea of surfing, huh?
20:
In that case, getting used to riding
the board on the ground—not on the
sea—should be the first step!
24: That might be a good idea.
28:
I suppose that makes sense. Just like
how the soldiers of Tris, who only
have a mind for swinging their
swords, are said to never miss a day
of practice...
32:
I, too, shall devote myself to training!
I ask for your support, everyone!
38:
Yep, yep. Can you handle the other
side, Stella?
54:
Prepare to be surprised like never
before.
58:
NWAAAH! Why, Aegis? Do you hate
being stepped on THAT much?
70:
The goal is to be mobile while
shielding my allies! I shan't give up
until I'm capable of that!
76:
Personally, I don't mind you as you
are now. I think you already put up a
fine defense for us.
83:
You trust in my cowardice but not in
my valor?!
84:
Watch as my knees tremble with all
the timidity of a newborn fawn just
dying to run off to its hiding place!
87: Well, why aren't you running then?
91:
Is it not obvious? The job of royalty is
to safeguard the citizenry.
94:
I doubt I am worthy of becoming
king, but that does not give me the
right to bring shame to those in my
family who truly deserve the title!
98:
That is my pride as royalty! I will not
use my cowardice as an excuse to
forfeit my duty!
104:
Although I've yet to grow
accustomed to it, I feel as if my
bond with Lord's Aegis has
strengthened.
107:
Nevertheless, I shall continue to
have faith! Ward thy people, Lord's
Aegis!
113:
He's keeping his balance. It's a
success.
118:
A "success"? Maybe we could call it
that if he could also control his
direction.
123: You seem to be having fun, Alk.
127: Oh yeah? Hm, maybe I am.
133:
Welp, it's time we went to save
Razelt again. We'll have to call
another ship.
135:
Mm-hm. He went straight ahead
this time, so he should be easy to
find.
139:
I just wonder if he's considered how
he's going to protect himself when
his shield's busy protecting others.
